THE STORY WAS ABOUT A BOY'S CHILDHOOD.
GROWING UP, HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY BECAUSE HIS FATHER WAS THE LIBRARY CUSTODIAN, AND AT THE TIME IT WAS SOMETIMES CUSTOM FOR JANITORIAL STAFF AND THEIR FAMILIES TO LIVE WHERE THEY WORKED.
THE BOY AT FIRST BELIEVED HE WAS RICH, BUT EVENTUALLY REALIZED THAT HIS LIVING SITUATION WAS JUST DIFFERENT THAN THOSE OF HIS PEERS.
HE WAS HESITANT TO INVITE OVER HIS PEERS BECAUSE HE WANTED TO FIT IN AND BE NORMAL.
BECAUSE HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY, HE AND HIS FAMILY HAD TO BE QUIET DURING THE DAY.
DURING THE NIGHT, HOWEVER, HE COULD BE AS LOUD AS HE WANTED, AND OFTEN CAME DOWN TO THE LIBRARY IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT TO READ.
HE BELIEVES HIS EXPERIENCES LIVING IN THE LIBRARY ARE WHAT GAVE HIM A HUNGER FOR KNOWLEDGE AND DROVE HIM TO BECOME A PROFESSOR.
UPON BRINGING HIS FATHER TO HIS SCHOOL TO SHOW HIM WHERE HE TAUGHT AND HIS NAME PLACARD, HIS FATHER WAS QUIET, BUT IT WAS CLEAR THAT HE WAS VERY MOVED BY HIS SON'S SUCCESS.
THIS SUCCESS AND DRIVE TO LEARN, THE MAN BELIEVED, RESULTED FROM HIS CHILDHOOD IN THE LIBRARY.
A BOY LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY AND IT WAS CUSTOM FOR HIM AND HIS FAMILY TO LIVE WHERE HE WORKED.
THE BOY DID NOT INVITE ANYONE TO HIS HOME BECAUSE HE WAS AFRAID OF BEING DIFFERENT.
DURING THE DAY, THE BOY HAD TO BE QUIET IN THE LIBRARY.
AT NIGHT, HOWEVER, HE COULD RUN AROUND AND MAKE AS MUCH NOISE AS HE WANTED.
HE OFTEN STAYED UP UNTIL 3 AM READING IN THE LIBRARY.
THE BOY EVENTUALLY BECAME A PROFESSOR, AND BROUGHT HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS SCHOOL AND NAME PLACARD.
HIS FATHER WAS QUIET, BUT IT WAS CLEAR HE WAS MOVED BY THE FACT THAT HIS SON HAD SUCCEED.
THE BOY (NOW A MAN) BELIEVES THAT HIS CHILDHOOD IN THE LIBRARY INSTILLED IN HIM A THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE AND LEAD HIM TO EVENTUALLY BECOMING A PROFESSOR.
